@node section1 "What is JZ Raw Download?"

                       @{b}Disclaimer:@{ub}

I accept no repsponsibility for any damage caused to software or hardware
through the direct or indirect use of this software. Using this software
is entirely at the users risk. By using this software you agree to the
above.

@{b}Liscence:@{ub}

This software is freely distributable providing that no charge is made
except for the reasonable costs of the media such as floppy disks or CDs.
You may not alter the binary in any way with the exception of crunching
(crunched versions are for personal use only and should not be distributed)
or archiving. All files which are part of the JZ Raw Dl distribution should
be included in the archive. Although this software is freely distributable
the copyright remains with the author.

                       @{b}What is it?@{ub}

A Raw download is sending a user a file which only exists on your hard
drive or a floppy disk and not actually in the BBS, filebase therefore a
user can not download the file in the normal way. JZ Raw DL provides an
easy way to allow the sysop to select a file or several files via a
reqtools requester to send to the user. JZ Raw DL is secure so users can
not access your hard drive.

@endnode

@node section3 "Installation on MAXs BBS"

                  @{b}Installation on MAXs BBS@{ub}

Setting it up is easy, just use the MAXs Function 34 for executing an
external door and enter the filename. The door can be stored anywhere you
like but a recommened path and filename is "Doors:JZRawDL/JZRawDL".


Key:   Function:   Extra:   Lo Acc:    Hi Acc:   Filename/Name/Dest/Path

 R        34         0       10000      10000     Doors:JZRawDL/JZRawDL


You should make the 'Lo Acc' 10000 because this door requires sysop
interaction at the local terminal. If there is no sysop around and the user
runs the door then the BBS will wait until the requestor is cancelled.

Requirements:

MaxsBBS 1.54 (should work with earlier versions) or any Maxs Compatible BBS
system such as Maxs Pro and MooSuck BBS.

You must have in your LIBS: drawer...

reqtools.library   - version 37 or later   

@endnode

